main event: Mr. BYERS reported observing an unidentified flying object over St. Paul, Minnesota, at approximately 1900L on 24 November 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as bright, round, and silver-colored, measuring 20-30 feet in diameter., The object hovered in the sky for approximately 10-15 minutes., There were no visible means of propulsion or exhaust trails., The object made a sudden and rapid vertical ascent before disappearing., A photograph of the object was obtained and submitted for analysis.
